From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 13:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] backends/monitor-manager: NULL-check logical_monitor before dereference

After meta_monitor_manager_rebuild() completes for a new config, callers
sometimes assume "monitor->current_mode != NULL => monitor->logical_monitor
!= NULL". That invariant is *not* upheld by the rebuild path: the
higher-level meta_monitor_manager_apply_monitors_config() runs
meta_monitor_update_current_mode() over every monitor after the rebuild,
which re-discovers current_mode from hardware CRTC state. A monitor whose
output is still assigned in hardware (e.g. just hot-plugged, or in a
transient state between config swaps) gets a non-NULL current_mode even
though it was not included in the new MetaMonitorsConfig and therefore was
never associated with a MetaLogicalMonitor by update_logical_state().

When this happens, two sites dereference NULL:

  - update_current_monitor_mode_scale (called via g_list_foreach over
    manager->monitors right after apply_monitors_config()) calls
    meta_logical_monitor_get_scale() on the NULL pointer -> SIGSEGV.
    Confirmed by coredump: PID 65271, /usr/bin/gnome-shell --mode=gdm,
    triggered by HP Reverb G2 EDID re-read storm.

  - handle_orientation_change passes the result to
    meta_logical_monitor_get_transform() without checking. Guarded by
    meta_monitor_is_active() but is_active checks current_mode, not
    logical_monitor, so the same invariant violation applies. Latent.

Apply the upstream pattern (already present at
meta_monitor_manager_get_monitor_for_connector, line 4211): guard the
dereference with a NULL check on the logical_monitor pointer. Return early
when there is no logical_monitor for this monitor -- the value cannot be
computed in that state, and the next rebuild that places the monitor into
a config will re-fire the relevant computations.

Forwarded: no
Last-Update: 2026-05-20
Index: mutter-50.1/src/backends/meta-monitor-manager.c
===================================================================
--- mutter-50.1.orig/src/backends/meta-monitor-manager.c
+++ mutter-50.1/src/backends/meta-monitor-manager.c
@@ -539,6 +539,17 @@ update_current_monitor_mode_scale (MetaM
     return;
 
   logical_monitor = meta_monitor_get_logical_monitor (monitor);
+  /* meta_monitor_update_current_mode() (called from the higher-level
+   * apply_monitors_config right before this foreach) can re-discover
+   * current_mode from hardware CRTC state and set it on monitors that
+   * are not part of the new MetaMonitorsConfig. Those monitors never
+   * had a logical_monitor assigned by update_logical_state(), so the
+   * implicit "current_mode => logical_monitor" invariant is broken
+   * here. Skip; the next rebuild that places this monitor into a
+   * config will recompute the scale. */
+  if (!logical_monitor)
+    return;
+
   scale = meta_logical_monitor_get_scale (logical_monitor);
 
   meta_monitor_set_default_scale (monitor, monitor_mode, scale);
@@ -905,6 +916,12 @@ handle_orientation_change (MetaOrientati
   transform = meta_orientation_to_transform (orientation);
 
   builtin_logical_monitor = meta_monitor_get_logical_monitor (builtin_monitor);
+  /* meta_monitor_is_active() above checks current_mode, not the
+   * logical_monitor pointer. They can disagree right after a config swap
+   * (see update_current_monitor_mode_scale comment), so guard the
+   * dereference here too. */
+  if (!builtin_logical_monitor)
+    return;
   panel_transform =
     meta_monitor_crtc_to_logical_transform (builtin_monitor, transform);
   if (meta_logical_monitor_get_transform (builtin_logical_monitor) ==
@@ -4205,10 +4222,21 @@ meta_monitor_manager_get_monitor_for_con
   for (l = manager->monitors; l; l = l->next)
     {
       MetaMonitor *monitor = l->data;
+      MetaLogicalMonitor *logical_monitor;
+
+      if (!meta_monitor_is_active (monitor))
+        continue;
+      if (g_strcmp0 (connector, meta_monitor_get_connector (monitor)) != 0)
+        continue;
+
+      /* Defensive: even with the meta_monitor_update_current_mode invariant
+       * fix, an external caller could still hit a transient state during
+       * rebuild. Prefer "not associated" over SIGSEGV. */
+      logical_monitor = meta_monitor_get_logical_monitor (monitor);
+      if (!logical_monitor)
+        return -1;
 
-      if (meta_monitor_is_active (monitor) &&
-          g_strcmp0 (connector, meta_monitor_get_connector (monitor)) == 0)
-        return meta_monitor_get_logical_monitor (monitor)->number;
+      return logical_monitor->number;
     }
 
   return -1;
